\
I stand by my earlier uninformed observation that the list should have been segmented by category. That would allow a nice deep dive into each "genre". For instance, I think there should be at least a couple more news people other than 
\b Walter the C
\b0  (maybe 
\b Mike Wallace
\b0  or 
\b Tom Brokaw
\b0  or even 
\b Matt Lauer
\b0 ). And no, 
\b Barbara Walters
\b0  is not a "newsie". She's a celebrity interview harpy.\
\
And, if you're not going to give too much love to the old school originators of the medium, you can't put 
\b Farrah Fawcett
\b0 , 
\b James Gandolfini
\b0  and 
\b Jennifer Aniston
\b0  on it. 1) Farrah is the poster girl for stained sheets. 2) You can't include an HBO show on the list -- no matter how popular it was. And 3) Aniston hasn't found a job since "Friends". Now that we've established some ground rules, let's do this...\
