\b\fs32 Complaints:
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720

\b \cf0 Bob Barker
\b0  (#34): Don't get me wrong -- I love's me some Bob Barker. But his career starts and stops with "The Price is Right". How the hell can he be #34 while 
\b Richard "tongue-kiss-me-darling" Dawson
\b0  is #95!!? Dawson was a star in his own right on "Hogan's Heroes", he was the oxygen for "Match Game" and was arguably more memorable (and unarguably more charismatic) on "Family Feud". That's injustice.\
\

\b Jerry Seinfeld
\b0  (#8): I know it was huge hit for 9 years. I know NBC lived and died by it. But #8 on the list? Can we take into account that none of the cast has been able to find meaningful employment for almost 10 years afterwards? It also didn't really influence any TV shows since. It was an oddball of a format, it worked for a long time and then went dormant like {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://biology.clc.uc.edu/steincarter/cicadas.htm"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \ul \ulc2 17 year cicadas}}. Methinks it could have been a little further down on the list.\
\
